00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:04.240
When I was a little girl, my father the King said...

00:02:04.240 --> 00:02:08.240
Mererid, I'm going to make you the priestess of our sacred well.

00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:13.240
Every day you must draw three buckets of water from the well and carry them for a mile.

00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:16.240
Then empty them into the river by the castle.

00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:19.240
A mile? That's a long way.

00:02:19.240 --> 00:02:20.240
Yep.

00:02:20.240 --> 00:02:21.240
Three buckets?

00:02:21.240 --> 00:02:22.240
Yep.

00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:23.240
Every morning?

00:02:23.240 --> 00:02:25.240
Yep. And every night.

00:02:25.240 --> 00:02:27.240
That's a lot of buckets.

00:02:27.240 --> 00:02:28.240
Yep.

00:02:28.240 --> 00:02:30.240
That's six buckets.

00:02:30.240 --> 00:02:33.240
Is it? Yes, I think so. Three plus three equals...

00:02:33.240 --> 00:02:35.240
It is, Dad. I know.

00:02:35.240 --> 00:02:39.240
I did GCSE maths at the Cantrigal College School for princesses.

00:02:39.240 --> 00:02:43.240
Well, anyway, this will all keep the spirit of the sacred well happy.

00:02:43.240 --> 00:02:46.240
Who, in turn, will keep everything happy in our kingdom.

00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:49.240
And what if I don't want to do it?

00:02:49.240 --> 00:02:53.240
Then the spirit of the sacred well will let fall a curse upon the land.

00:02:53.240 --> 00:02:55.240
What kind of curse?

00:02:55.240 --> 00:02:56.240
Not a clue.

00:02:56.240 --> 00:02:59.240
Anyone ever seen this spirit?

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:03.240
Nope. It's a bit like the god of the 21st century.

00:03:03.240 --> 00:03:04.240
The who of the what?

00:03:04.240 --> 00:03:06.240
The god of the 21st century.

00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:09.240
In the future, it hasn't happened yet.

00:03:09.240 --> 00:03:12.240
You never see him, but you have to believe.

00:03:12.240 --> 00:03:15.240
Hmm. Not sure I do.

00:03:15.240 --> 00:03:22.240
Well, here I am, 16 years later, carrying those buckets.

00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:27.240
I've been doing it for so many years now that I've really had enough.

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:31.240
My hands hurt. More than anything, my hands hurt.

00:03:31.240 --> 00:03:35.240
My legs feel heavy. Gravity is constantly against me.

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:39.240
But I can't disappoint my dad.

00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:42.240
Don't want to be a failure.

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:45.240
And with this curse, I've got no choice anyway.

00:03:45.240 --> 00:03:49.240
Oh well. No more complaining.

00:03:49.240 --> 00:03:52.240
Just get on with it.

00:03:52.240 --> 00:03:55.240
The locals watch Merarid come and go.

00:03:56.240 --> 00:04:00.240
Every day she goes past here with her buckets.

00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:04.240
My name's Matt. I've lived in Canterbury all my life.

00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:07.240
Working in the fields.

00:04:07.240 --> 00:04:11.240
Now and again, I like to pop down to my local Canterbury Railroad pub

00:04:11.240 --> 00:04:15.240
for an occasional pint of Guinness. Just the odd one.

00:04:15.240 --> 00:04:17.240
The odd one, did you say, Grandad?

00:04:17.240 --> 00:04:19.240
I think it might be a few more than that.

00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:22.240
Well, I reckon I deserve it, Siwan.

00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:26.240
So I watch her go past every day with her buckets

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:29.240
and I think not much of a life is it for a young woman.

00:04:29.240 --> 00:04:31.240
I wouldn't like it.

00:04:31.240 --> 00:04:34.240
Just lately, I see her looking more and more fed up.

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:37.240
There'll be trouble there one day, Siwan. You mark my words.

00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:40.240
She won't put up with it forever.

00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:45.240
On a fine day, when I'm in the park garden outside, you can hear her muttering.

00:04:45.240 --> 00:04:49.240
Why must I do this? Is it even necessary?

00:04:49.240 --> 00:04:54.240
Would anyone even notice if I just didn't?

00:04:54.240 --> 00:04:56.240
What would happen?

00:04:56.240 --> 00:04:59.240
What would be the consequences?

00:04:59.240 --> 00:05:04.240
I hate lugging these horrible, heavy buckets around.

00:05:04.240 --> 00:05:07.240
If I could stop doing it, I would.

00:05:07.240 --> 00:05:11.240
I want to lose this heavy burden once and for all.

00:05:11.240 --> 00:05:14.240
I want to be free.

00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:16.240
But there's the curse.

00:05:16.240 --> 00:05:19.240
