00:08:21.240 --> 00:08:24.240
And the next thing I know, I hear these drums.

00:08:24.240 --> 00:08:29.240
And they get closer and closer. I'm watching the vibrations of them in my pint.

00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:33.240
Then there's a silence. And I'm just about to take a drink.

00:08:33.240 --> 00:08:38.240
When the next minute a window breaks and a man hurls through it.

00:08:38.240 --> 00:08:46.240
And then a whole horde of men come clashing in, fighting over falling in the pub soldiers.

00:08:46.240 --> 00:08:49.240
Grandad! Grandad! Are you in there?

00:08:49.240 --> 00:08:52.240
Come on, you need to leave. There's a battle going on.

00:08:52.240 --> 00:09:00.240
I grab my pint and I try dodging all the fists to make it to Sion at the back door.

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:05.240
Next thing, a white goat comes running through the door.

00:09:05.240 --> 00:09:11.240
And knocks me off my feet, leaving me and my pint on the floor.

00:09:11.240 --> 00:09:15.240
So I help him up. Grandad, not the goat.

00:09:15.240 --> 00:09:20.240
Suddenly we're stuck in the middle of a battle. I'm lucky to make it home alive.

00:09:20.240 --> 00:09:24.240
What a night. All I wanted was a quiet pint.

00:09:24.240 --> 00:09:30.240
In the battle, it is Rodri's invading army that is defeated, not the army of Cantigualod.

00:09:30.240 --> 00:09:36.240
So Mereyd's plan fails. Prince Rodri has taken prisoner. He is furious.

00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:41.240
That wretch Mereyd. She lied. This country isn't weak at all.

00:09:41.240 --> 00:09:47.240
How dare she whisper poison in my ears. Make me risk my men. All my people.

00:09:47.240 --> 00:09:51.240
Why did I fall for such a pretty face and pretty allies?

00:09:51.240 --> 00:09:57.240
I wish I could go back in time and cover my ears. Protect them from the poison that slowly seeped into them.

00:09:57.240 --> 00:10:06.240
